node.text: which was directly hit by eye of #Ida! Major damage all around…We’ve been serving hot @WCKitchen meals along the way as people lost everything. They wouldn’t let us in the shelter so we setup outside & everyone came anyway 🤷‍♂️ #ChefsForLouisiana

node.text: Reporting from our friends AJ’s Produce in New Orleans…no electricity but they jumped in to support! WCK team has been cooking non-stop because no power means no food or shops…We’ve seen many people desperate for a meal…

node.text: I’m on the ground in New Orleans with @natemook & WCK’s Relief team…Winds are getting bad as Hurricane #Ida makes landfall…We have 3 kitchens ready with supplies already for 100,000+ meals! Now we will shelter until Ida passes… #ChefsForLouisiana

node.text: Thank you from the bottom of my heart. No single donation or gesture by itself can end hunger. But today we write a new chapter—no action too small, no idea too bold, no problem too big for us to solve together.

node.text: Reporting from our friends AJ’s Produce in New Orleans…no electricity but they jumped in to support! WCK team has been cooking non-stop because no power means no food or shops…We’ve seen many people desperate for a meal…

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jose Andres on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and outdoors.

node.text: Hola from New Orleans! 👋 @WCKitchen team is safe after Hurricane #Ida…But no power here & maybe not for days or more! We already are serving hot pasta, sandwiches, fruit to hungry families…Also just delivered to Emergency Ops Center & cleanup crews in street! #ChefsForLouisiana

node.text: Most buildings are damaged or destroyed, including this Catholic Church. @WCKitchen is delivering meals daily & our friends @CoreResponse are also here clearing rubble so communities can start rebuilding… #ChefsForHaiti

node.text: What’s happening in Afghanistan breaks my heart…but the outpouring of support from people across America helps glue it back ❤️‍🩹 Our @WCKitchen team at Dulles Airport saw even more refugees today….They had to go bring hundreds of extra meals & are still serving! #ChefsForAfghans

node.text: Hola from Jeremie in Haiti! 👋 We are delivering meals with @WCKitchen partner HHF… I’m at the bridge that was damaged in the earthquake so trucks can’t cross safely. Instead we use this fleet of motorbikes to get food across the river…Adaptation is key! #ChefsForHaiti

node.text: REPORT from Rambo in Haiti! This is a town near Maniche where we @wckitchen have been serving meals…Many homes damaged or totally destroyed here. And this is all these families have! I brought 200 sandwiches…and we will deliver hot food through road from Maniche. #ChefsForHaiti
